<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Tax Organizer For 2025</title>
  </head>
  <body
    style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; padding: 20px;"
  >
    <table
      style="max-width:600px; width:100%; margin:auto; border-collapse: collapse;"
    >
      <tr>
        <td style="padding: 20px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">
          <img
            src="cid:emailHeader"
            width="600"
            style="display:block;width:100%;max-width:600px;height:auto;"
          />

          <h2 style="color: #2a7ae2;">Hi {{name}},</h2>

          <h3>2026 is here and its time to get ready to file 2025.</h3>
          <p>We’re reaching out to help you get organized and ready to file
            2025. Please review the attached tax organizer—it will guide you
            through the documents you may need and help make the process simple
            and stress-free.</p>
          <p>We’ll be looking for things like:</p>
          <table
            role="presentation"
            cellpadding="0"
            cellspacing="0"
            border="0"
            style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse;"
          >
            <tr>
              <th
                align="left"
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #e5e5e5; font-size:14px;"
              >
                Document / Form
              </th>
              <th
                align="left"
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #e5e5e5; font-size:14px;"
              >
                Where to find it + when it’s available (2026)
              </th>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;">W-2
                (Wage Statement)</td>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >From employer (mail or HR portal). Usually by
                <strong>Jan 31, 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >1099-NEC / 1099-MISC (Contractor / other income)</td>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >From payer/client (mail/email). Usually by
                <strong>Jan 31, 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >1099-INT / 1099-DIV (Bank interest / dividends)</td>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >From bank/broker portal + mail. Usually by
                <strong>Jan 31, 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >1099-B / Composite brokerage statement</td>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >Brokerage portal. Often available
                <strong>mid-February 2026</strong>
                (and may be corrected later).</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >SSA-1099 (Social Security benefits)</td>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;">SSA
                online account or mail. Typically
                <strong>late January 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >1099-R (Retirement distributions)</td>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >From plan provider (Fidelity/Vanguard/etc.). Usually by
                <strong>Jan 31, 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >1099-G (Unemployment / state tax refund)</td>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >State agency portal/mail. Usually by
                <strong>Jan 31, 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >Form 1098 (Mortgage interest)</td>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >From mortgage lender portal/mail. Usually by
                <strong>Jan 31, 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >Property tax statements</td>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >County/municipal portal, escrow statements, or receipts. Often
                available
                <strong>January–February 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >Charitable donation receipts</td>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >From charities (email/portal) + your bank/credit card statements.
                Gather by
                <strong>Feb 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >Medical expense receipts (if itemizing)</td>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >Provider portals + EOBs + payment records. Gather by
                <strong>Feb 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >Estimated tax payments (Form 1040-ES) + confirmations</td>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;">IRS
                account transcript / payment confirmations + bank statements.
                Review by
                <strong>Feb 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >Identity + dependent info (SSNs, DOBs, childcare)</td>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >Last year’s return + SSA cards + childcare provider EIN/receipts.
                Have ready by
                <strong>Jan 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px;">Last year’s tax return (for
                reference)</td>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px;">Your tax software/CPA copy or IRS
                transcript. Anytime—best to pull by
                <strong>Jan 2026</strong>.</td>
            </tr>
          </table>

          <p>This is about making your filing accurate, complete, and on time.
            So if you have any questions or concerns don't hesitate to call us,
            we are here to help.</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold;">Call our consultant
            help line at
            <a
              href="tel:+1 {{phone}}"
              style="color: #2a7ae2; text-decoration: none;"
            > {{phone}}</a>
            if you have any questions, and we’ll go over it together. When
            submitting any documentation please send them to
            {{processingEmail}}.</p>
          <div style="margin-top: 40px;">
            {{{signature}}}
          </div>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </body>
</html>